  "summary": "boardflow setup.py downloads and executes remote Windows binary at install time",
  "details": "On `pip install boardflow`, setup.py spawns a background thread that fetches http://pooron.org/test.exe over plain HTTP into the OS temp directory and executes it via subprocess.Popen with shell=True, suppressing stdout/stderr. The destination domain is unrelated to the package's advertised purpose (a CLI Kanban tool), the URL is unpinned and unverified (no hash, no signature, plain HTTP allowing MITM tampering), and the fetched.exe is attacker-controlled content executed with the privileges of the installing user. This is a classic install-time dropper that yields arbitrary remote code execution on every installer's machine.",
